"It is the long term investor, he who most promotes the public
interest, who will in practice come in for the most criticism,
wherever investment funds are managed by committees or boards or
banks. For it is in the essence of his behaviour that he should be
eccentric, unconventional and rash in the eyes of average opinion. If
he is successful, that will only confirm the general belief in his
rashness; and if in the short run he is unsuccessful, which is very
likely, he will not receive much mercy. Worldly wisdom teaches that it
is better for reputations to fail conventionally than succeed
unconventionally."  -- John Maynard Keynes

