"With most stocks, a low price/earnings ratio is a good thing, but not
with cyclicals. When the p/e ratios of cyclical companies are very
low, it's usually a sign that they are at the end of a prosperous
interlude... Soon the economy will falter, and the earnings of the
cyclical will decline at breathtaking speed. As more investors head
for the exits, the stock price will plummet. Buying a cyclical after
several years of record earnings and when the p/e ratio has hit a low
point is a proven method for losing half your money in a short period
of time."  -- Peter Lynch

